1. Create a user account on Github.  Here there has to provide a username and email.  

2. Select repositories and create a new repository. 

3. Create files in an editor or IDE of choice. 

4. To make a basic level personal web page use HTML code, displaying your name, followed by a picture of yourself. Provide the HTML code file and the picture file, along with any supplementary files in a folder.

5. Drag and drop the file contents of the folder to upload them to Github 

6. Commit the changes and the repository name (e.g. username.github.io) becomes a URL.
